      <title>Re: Cost for lv up smithing</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12700#M12700</link>
      <description>I presume you are talking GM DoN cultural armor. The masters stuff has trivials up to 304 and the GM stuff is as high as 384. With a geerlok,&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;success formula = skill*1.05 + 50 - trivial*0.75  &lt;&lt;&lt;--- is this still valid?&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You need 275 base skill to have a 50% chance on a GM chest piece.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Roughly, it takes 100pp to hit 100 skill, 10kpp for 200, 200kpp for 250. Much, much more for 300. At 1:20 skill-up chance, 30 skill points (180-210) in EVB could cost 30*20*111pp = 67kpp. (111pp = 2 velium pieces from bazaar + coldain temper)&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Also, it can take considerable time farming materials once you get beyond fine plate (180ish).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You are in for a world of hurt ;)</description>
