      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;ether_sphynx wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Roughly, it takes 100pp to hit 100 skill, 10kpp for 200, 200kpp for 250. Much, much more for 300. At 1:20 skill-up chance, 30 skill points (180-210) in EVB could cost 30*20*111pp = 67kpp. (111pp = 2 velium pieces from bazaar + coldain temper)&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;It depends on how you skill up.  You could do Shadowscream all the way to like 260 (or something like that) and farm everything yourself.  It would be pretty cheap to do (far less than 200K, but take a lot of time.)  Or you could use the cultural to skill up, which would be quicker but more expensive, as Ether says. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;For the velium, I wouldn't buy it in the bazaar.  You can break down velium weapons now, so you can get enough pretty quickly.  So it's just the cost of the temper for that. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
