    <item>
      <title>Re: Cost for lv up smithing</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Trade&amp;message.id=12714#M12714</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;I went back and found what I had posted on EQ traders after I skilled up on MCS.  I found that, in my case at least, the usual estimates were high.  It cost me, by my estimates, about 55K to go from 222 to 251 on MCS - with selling the MCS in the bazaar at 200 pp each (they tribute for like 1300 so sell very quickly at that price).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I should note that I had BSM 3 and salvage 3 when I did this - I'm sure that made a significant difference in cost. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And I agree that the estimates for EVB are way too high.  You can easily farm the velium yourself, and even if you don't, smart buying in the bazaar will net you velium pieces at 5 to 10 pp each  (buy blocks and large bricks and cut them down - people often don't price those proportionately).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
